  "prompt": "What are the symptoms of a heart cancer?",
  "response": "Heart cancer, or primary cardiac tumors, are extremely rare. When they do occur, the symptoms can be quite varied and might resemble those of other heart conditions. Some potential symptoms of heart cancer include:\n\n1. **Chest Pain**: This can be similar to angina and may be caused by the tumor pressing on surrounding tissues.\n\n2. **Arrhythmias**: Irregular heartbeats or palpitations may occur if the tumor affects the electrical pathways of the heart.\n\n3. **Shortness of Breath**: This can happen if the tumor obstructs blood flow or affects heart function.\n\n4. **Fatigue**: General tiredness and weakness may be present due to the heart's reduced efficiency.\n\n5. **Swelling in the Legs or Abdomen**: This can result from fluid accumulation due to impaired heart function.\n\n6. **Heart Murmurs**: Abnormal heart sounds might be detected during a physical examination.\n\n7. **Fever**: In some cases, an unexplained fever can occur.\n\n8. **Weight Loss**: Unintentional weight loss may be a sign of malignancy.\n\n9. **Symptoms of Heart Failure**: Such as swelling (edema), particularly in the legs, ankles, and feet, and difficulty lying flat.\n\nBecause these symptoms can be indicative of various heart conditions, it is crucial to consult a healthcare professional for accurate diagnosis and appropriate management.",
